 America\n*[[Global horizontal sounding technique]], an atmospheric field research project in the late 1960s\n*[[Juliet Marine Systems Ghost]], watercraft\n*[[Rolls-Royce Ghost]], car\n\n==See also==\n*[[Apparition (disambiguation)]]\n*[[GH057ayame]] (born 1988), gamertag of Eric Hewitt, professional ''Halo'' player\n*[[Ghost in the machine (disambiguation)]]\n*[[Ghost Island (disambiguation)]]\n*[[Ghost pepper]] (''Bhut jolokia'')\n*[[Ghost town (disambiguation)]]\n*[[Ghost train (disambiguation)]]\n*[[Ghosted (disambiguation)]]\n*[[Ghosting (disambiguation)]]\n*[[Haunted house]]\n*[[Phantom (disambiguation)|Phantom]]\n*{{Look from|Ghost}}\n\n{{disambiguation}}\n", "text_old": "{{wiktionary|ghost}}\nA '''[[ghost]]''' is a spirit of a dead person that may appear to the living.\n\n'''Ghost''' or '''Ghosts''' may also refer to:\n{{TOC right}}\n==People==\n*[[Ghost (producer)]], British hip hop producer\n*[[Ghost (Reggae)]] (born 1974), singer\n*[[Robert Guerrero]] (born 1983), a.k.a. The Ghost, American boxer\n*[[Ivan L. Moody]] (born 1980), a.k.a. Ghost, member of Five Finger Death Punch\n*[[Kelly Pavlik]] (born 1982), a.k.a. The Ghost, American boxer\n*[[Styles P]] (born 1974), a.k.a. The Ghost, American rapper\n\n== Arts, entertainment, and media==\n===Fictional entities===\n*[[Ghost (comics)]], several characters and publications\n*[[Ghost (Dungeons & Dragons)|Ghost (''Dungeons & Dragons'')]]\n*[[Ghost (Hamlet)|Ghost (''Hamlet'')]], character from William Shakespeare's play ''Hamlet''\n*[[Ghost (The Matrix)|Ghost (''The Matrix'')]], a character in ''Enter the Matrix''\n*Ghost, the robotic companion of guardians in ''[[Destiny (video game)|Destiny]]''\n*Ghost, a character in the novel ''[[Lost Souls (Poppy Z. Brite novel)|Lost Souls]]''\n*Ghost, a [[Gameplay of Pok\u00e9mon|type of Pok\u00e9mon]]\n**[[Haunter]], a Pok\u00e9mon known in Japan as Ghost\n*[[Ghosts (Pac-Man)|Ghosts (''Pac-Man'')]], the recurring antagonists in the ''Pac-Man'' franchise\n* Ghosts, group